  "name": "Morrison COU1 — ML-augmented CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a hybrid CFD/ML hemolysis prediction pipeline applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. A gradient-boosted surrogate model (XGBoost) is trained on CFD-derived shear-stress histories to predict the relative hemolysis index (RH) across 5 flow-speed operating points. COU1 evaluates whether the computational-plus-ML model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Robustness of the ML surrogate to input distribution shift is noted as a topic studied separately; no linked evidence is provided.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-rh-criterion",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-ml-surrogate-identifies-worst-case-hemolysis",
