      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the quantity mandated by FDA guidance for comparative hemolysis assessment of blood-contacting devices. The surrogate is trained to predict RH directly from shear-stress history features, ensuring the model output is the exact quantity required for the regulatory decision."
