  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-ml-hemolysis-cou1-decision",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels at Model Risk Level 2. The XGBoost surrogate demonstrates strong nominal-condition predictive accuracy (R² = 0.97, max RH deviation 8.3%) and correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions relative to the predicate device. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. The assessment team notes that robustness of the ML surrogate under input distribution shift (manufacturing variability beyond the training envelope, patient-population blood property variation, intraoperative transients) has been identified as a topic for separate study; however, this evidence is not linked in the present package and was not required for acceptance at MRL 2. The package is accepted for the stated COU.",
